values:
So for the first time in my life, I am excited for the summer.  Here's why:

1) Nutmeg is coming home which means 3M will be at full strength and there will be plenty of blonde outings; kayaking, gregg's, road trips,etc.

2) Zipper gets a haircut for the summer and Zipper looks much better with a haircut

3) My bedroom at home is being redone, this week it is being painted pink and I will be rearranging the furniture and selecting window treatments with la mia madre

4) My room is much bigger than the glorified closet refered to as a dorm room

5) I'm taking recent fiction which should hopefully be a fun class

6) I'm a little excited to go to work and do something productive and get to dress up everyday

7) I have a bigger tv in my room than I do at school

8) the weather should hopefully be getting nice soon

So I'm very excited about the summer and I will be turning 20!  Finally I will no longer be a teenager. 

I'm excited for next year too.  I'm commuting, and I think that should be an interesting change(no more donnovan food) and I'm taking 2 british lit classes, 2 writing classes, and forensic science.  and i'm just in a good place in my life right now, and i feel as if i'm ready to move on with my life.  

I came to the conclusion, well I came to this conclusion a few weeks ago actually, that I'm really quite different from the majority of my peers.  I mean I'm actually capable of thinking independently, I have morals, and I can hold intelligent conversation.  The majority of my friends possess the same qualities and are among the reasons that are generation is not totally going to fuck up everything.  

of course i'm suffering from the usual grade paranoia, and you know what that means...i'm going be looking for boxes for mine and mattie camp's street home.  so you know if anybody has any like really big boxes, you may want to put them aside just in case.

The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who have a split personality - cold as ice on the outside but hot as fire in the heart.
In love, you feel the most alive when things are straight-forward, and you're told that you're loved.
You'd like to your lover to think you are loyal and faithful... that you'll never change.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is comforting. You crave a relationship where you always feel warmth and love.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred.
In this moment, you think of love as something you thirst for. You'll do anything for love, but you won't fall for it easily.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

the parental units are being such Orwellian facists.  So my bedroom at home is being redone and it's going to be painted pink and there has always been a cross(they put up)in my room.  Well it is required that either that cross remains up or another one is placed up in its place.  Which is just bullshit!  There needs to be a cross in every room in the house according to them.  I go to their fucking Catholic church, is that not enough?  I do not believe the majority of Catholic doctrine and I do not believe that Jesus is the Jesus of Catholics.  I mean I believe he was the greatest person that walked this earth, was a great prophet, and definately a good person to model your life after, but I don't believe that he's God.  I never have.  To me there's God-just one God that's it, not a whole three persons in one thing.  So if I don't prescribe to the belief, why should I have to follow it.  I am tired of having Christianity shoved down my throat.  I respect the fact that they are wicked Catholic and that's a large part of the reason why I haven't converted to anything else.  That and the fact that I'm not a big fan of organized religion to begin with and you know what, I don't think any of them have it completely right.  They also are completely unable to even accept the possibility of me having add.  Ironically they agree that adderall(which is practically the same as ritalin)has been working wonders on me.  Besides that I'm really happy and content, really, I just needed to get that little rant out.

last night I went to see Kelly Clarkson with my dad, it was wicked good.  She only performed for an hour and 15 mintues(much shorter than Clay's concerts) and she's not as much of an entertainer as him, but she's a much stronger singer.  She has like long straight blonde hair now and she looked wicked good.  Graham Colton band opened for her and they were pretty good, my dad when they come out screams, "We want Kelly".  It was the second best concert I've been to, the first Clay concert I went to was by far the best concert ever.  Kelly was like very down-to-earth and stuff and she seemed to be having a lot of fun on stage.  My dad bought me twizzlers and diet coke at the show, that was wicked exciting.  There were like a lot of screaming teenage girls there, so it was really hard to hear her and the other band at times.  Like every single song everyone was singing a long really loud.  We had a completely unobstructed perfect view of the stage so that was wicked nice.  She sang "Behind My Hazel Eyes", "The Trouble with Love" and "Miss Independent" so that greatly excited me, sadly she did not sing "Low"(that was my biggest disappoint with the concert).

So i've been thinking a lot and I realized that I get attached to people way too easily and I trust everyone is a good person(for the greater part)and I expect them to be like to me(to a degree).  I also have the tendency to assume that just because someone is my best friend at some point we will always be best friend.  I think this is one of the things that makes me so emotionally fragile and leads to be being hurt a lot.  Honestly, when things don't work out between me and a guy, I rarely cry or am that upset over, but loosing a friend is like wicked tramatic for me.  I've spent all year trying to figure out a solution to me being less vunerable, but in a way I don't want to.  I mean it's partially what makes me so unique, I do tend to see the good in people and love my friends more than anything else in the world.  And I mean if I wasn't so trusting, I would not be Maria, so I guess it's kind of a good thing that I'm so trusting.  But the whole being emotionally fragile thing is a bitch.  Like i have such a strong innate desire for everyone to love me and to please everyone.  Honestly, my ideal concept of the world would be where everybody loves me and everybody is friends and nice to each other and respects everyone(which is wicked cheesy, but whatever).  It just makes me so sad sometimes that at one point somebody can be one of your best friends and then later not even give two shits about your life.  I can't be like that though, no matter how badly somebody who I considered one of my true friends screws me over, I still truely wish that we were still close, and I still want to for them to be happy.  I think from now on whenever somebody reaches my higher echelon of friends I should have them sign some type of agreement saying they won't ever hurt me to avoid this type of pain.  Of course I truly believe that Michelle and Meg are the best friends in the world and would never talk shit about me or fuck me over, so that makes everything better.  but like still i hate people that are not loyal.  I remember junior yr retreat at LaSalle when we were seperated into 2 separate groups and people had to list personality traits of people in the other group, on my paper it said:
Quiet/Reserved/Talkative
Loyal
Hard-working
Funny
Musical
I think my list was pretty accurate.  I really don't know what the purpose of this entry was...I really admire anyone who reads me lj and can acutally make sense of it.

in an effort to put off starting research for my lit study paper as long as possible, i have decided to list what i believe to be the best CDs ever(these are in no particular order).

1)"Breakaway"-Kelly Clarkson: every song on this album is incredible and she has such an awesome voice.  the best song on it in my opinion is "Behind my Hazel Eyes" which i've heard will be the next single.

2)"Measure of a Man"-Clay Aiken: i think everyone knows why i think this cd is so great

3)"All the Way"-Celine Dion: her music can be cheesy, but when you're in a bad mood or like a mellow want to listen to lite rock 105 kinda mood this cd is perfect, and she does have an incredible voice

4)"Tapestry"-Carole King: this is just such an incredible album, she is amazing and her songs still get played today "Where you Lead"(gilmore girls theme), "Natural Woman", and "I feel the earth move".

5)American Wedding Soundtrack: every song on this soundtrack is awesome and perfect for listening in the car.

6)"Affirmation"-Savage Garden:i miss savage garden why did they have to break up?

7)"Jingle Bell Rock"-Brenda Lee:i've loved this album since i was 4.

8)"Replay"-Play: a total girl power CD

9)Greg Raposo-his CD is fun.

10)Barenaked Laides-"All their Greatest Hits-disc one": this album has "If I had a million dollars" and "Shoebox" all on one album...it's just greatness.

11)Michelle Branch-her first album is so great and all the songs i can totally relate to

12)Cherie-she has such an awesome voice and she has some pretty good songs, including a cover of "It's Your Love" that I think she sounds better than Tim McGraw on

13)"Jagged Little Pill"-Alanis Morisette: i first bought this when i was 10 yrs old and I still know the words to every song and can still listen to it and enjoy it just like i did 9 yrs ago.

14)"Songs About Jane"-Maroon 5

15)Elton John-"Greatest Hits": "Crocodile Rock", "Your Song" and "Don't Let the Sun Go Down On Me" are some of the greatest songs ever.

16)A Walk to Remember Soundtrack

17)"1"-The Beatles

18)"So Much for the Afterglow"-Everclear: their cover of "Brown Eyed Girl" makes me deliriously happy

so i just read something in alex's lj about how the providence journal wrote that 60% of ric students fail to graduate in 6 years.  i think it's time we increase our admission standards, i could see failing to get out in 4-but do you really need 6+ years to get your BA?  they way it looks now, i'm going to be out in 4-as long as they continue to have writing classes when i need them.

i got my lit study paper back(the one the majority of the class got either a d/f on) and she had a B- crossed out and then a C+.  i wish she would have just put the C+ cause now i'm like wtf i almost got a B-.  i was ecstatic that i got a C+ on her paper which is quite a change considering the fact that usually I feel like a failure when I get an A- on papers.  we have the option of rewriting this one, but it's only 10% of our grade and the most i can get is like an 86(and that's only if i get an A on the rewrite which i highly doubtful)and the paper was on like the most boring repetitive thing ever, so i am not rewriting.

i slept till 12 today.  did not go to psych, but our grade is based on tests only(which so far i have an A average)and i just fall asleep when i go.  everything i knew on the first exam was from reading the textbook.

my uncle graduated from RIC in 69(it only took him 4 years) and he had my children's lit professor for creative writing and western lit.  that was actually like his fave professor.  if it wasn't for McSweeney my uncle would have been forced into leaving for the air force and not getting to finish his BA.  according to my uncle McSweeney like wrote some letter to a senator or something.  my uncle was like so wicked excited that i have him.

so my uncle went to brussels over his february vacation and he got a bunch of those elastic type bracelets(like the ones they have for breast cancer and the lance armstrong ones)and his say count me blue and they are like bright blue.  they're some like anti bush thing, so he gives me one and my mom goes, "the dog has a collar that color, zipper's anti bush too." it was pretty funny.

so hiliary clinton is the front runner so far for the democratic party and condolezza rice may actually get the other party's nom.  i'm really hoping this happens and the two run against each other becuase all the anti-women people will vote for nader and his party will finally get the 5% they need, he might actually get enough that he actually becomes president.  although i think hiliary would make a good president.

i hate winter.  i want spring to be here already.
